# Unreal conventions

- Target Unreal Engine 5.6 or later and use Unreal naming conventions.
- Keep gameplay/UI in `SFRouteRacer`, runtime geospatial code in `SFGeoRuntime`,
  and editor dependencies in `SFRouteRacerEditor`.
- Prefer subsystems over global singletons and avoid unnecessary Tick functions.
- Validate schema versions and references before creating map actors.
- Keep routing graph logic separate from rendered road geometry.
- Put Blueprints behind C++ systems and use them for visual assembly and tuning.
- Add automation tests for parsing, coordinates, routing, and race transitions.
